4	Federal Marriage Amendment - Wikipedia	The Federal Marriage Amendment (FMA) is a proposed amendment to the United  States Constitution which would define marriage in the United States as a union  of one man and one woman. The FMA would also prevent judicial extension of  marriage rights to same-sex or other unmarried heterosexual couples.	https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_Marriage_Amendment
